The non-resonant strategy can control the phase shift of the wavefronts that interact with the nanostructures by adjusting the effective refractive index, which is determined by the periodicity, diameter, and height of the meta-atoms at a subwavelength scale (Fig. 3(e)), or by exploiting the geometric phase (Fig. 3(f)). The former propagation phase is stimulated by waveguides or waveguide-like modes without polarization selection [100, 116–118] and can be derived as [119]2φ=2πλ0neffH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
