Equation (6) and (7) show that the output electric fields consist of two orthogonal circular polarizations (CPs). The second term on the right side of Eq. (6) and (7) implies that the transmitted or reflected light acquires an opposite-handedness and is simultaneously phase-shifted by argtx/rx-ty/ry2±2θ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
