In addition, a detour phase modulation strategy has also been reported to control the propagation phase along a different direction from the incident one [127, 128]. The principle of the detour phase modulation is shown in Fig. 4(a) [129]. When a light shines on two adjacent meta-atoms, it will be diffracted and produce a second wave of identical phase. With regard to the diffraction wave at a fixed refraction angle θ, the corresponding phase difference Δφ can be derived as8Δφ=2πDsinθ/λ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
